{"_id":"24KQiXOhiDL3CSL2","name":"Fran Claybrook","content":"<div style=\"font-family:Signika;text-align:justify;font-size:14px;margin-top:2rem;margin-left:2rem\">\n<div><img style=\"border-radius:50%;border:2px solid black;box-shadow:0 0 25px #484444\" src=\"modules/sanseer/media/journals/characters/close-ups/claybrook-fran.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></div>\n<hr />\n<h2>Who is Fran Claybrook?</h2>\n</div>","img":"modules/sanseer/media/journals/characters/portraits/claybrook-fran.jpg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"y4pRACjo50IZ62pc":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"5MkBZkSfl3WBwwz9","name":"Variachel Dawnrage","content":"<div style=\"font-family:Signika;text-align:justify;font-size:14px;margin-top:2rem;margin-left:2rem\">\n<div><img style=\"border-radius:50%;border:2px solid black;box-shadow:0 0 25px #484444\" src=\"modules/sanseer/media/journals/characters/close-ups/dawnrage-variachel.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></div>\n<hr />\n<p>A warrior in the ancient legends. Lost her mother and father to <em>urch</em> and her sister Valherys to the ravages of deceitful, licentious men. Her vengeance was upon them served cold and was dreadful in its nature. After, she fled in despair but found friends who saved her. The light was brought back into her life on meeting @JournalEntry[hwLyX9WDnl7elFvI]{Charlon Lugera}, a warrior and her passionate lover. Their adventures took them to the depths of the world where Charlon was lost, giving her life for Variachel. Variachel dedicated her life to bringing Charlon back from the afterlife.</p>\n<p>After once more descending into the abyss to pull the world from the brink of Hell, Variachel was rewarded with the return of Charlon. Legend says the two left the embattled lands behind and lived out the remainder of their lives in peace.</p>\n</div>","img":"modules/sanseer/media/journals/characters/portraits/dawnrage-variachel.jpg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"y4pRACjo50IZ62pc":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"5ajF7W0RKb261nGq","name":"Cassandra's Daggers","content":"<div style=\"font-family:Signika;text-align:justify;font-size:14px;margin-top:2rem;margin-left:2rem\">\n<h3>Cassandra Brakefield's Sacrificial Daggers</h3>\n<p>Â </p>\n<p>The wooden casket contained two ornate daggers. They are the same other than the material from which they are made. They each have a rather cruel, hooked blade.</p>\n<p>Both look ceremonial. Each alone would perhaps be worth money, although it may be surmised that they are more valuable as a pair.</p>\n<p>However, something about them tells you that</p>\n<ul>\n<li>They would probably not sell - at least not to a simple collector.</li>\n<li>The kind of person who <em>would</em> wish to acquire such artefacts would pay very very highly.</li>\n<li>The kind of person who would wish to acquire such artefacts would probably have you killed after the transaction.</li>\n<li>They may be of use later on.</li>\n</ul>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>The daggers have a reputation. Where and how Cassandra Brakefield obtained them is unknown at this time - try asking her - but they are potent.</p>\n<p>As a pair they are known as</p>\n<p><strong>The Heartseeker Blades</strong></p>\n<p>They have in the past been used during the sacrifice of a virginal female in order to subsume her youth. They donate longevity to the sacrificer as long as the ritual is carried out in precise ways. The sacrifice also endows beauty to those who are not or enhances the power of attraction in those already possessed of beauty.</p>\n</section>\n</div>","img":"modules/sanseer/media/journals/miscellaneous/cassandras-blades.jpg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"y4pRACjo50IZ62pc":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"5qnDNNxyy3XfUjik","name":"Cassandra Brakefield","content":"<div style=\"font-family:Signika;text-align:justify;font-size:14px;margin:2rem\">\n<div><img style=\"border-radius:50%;border:2px solid black;box-shadow:0 0 25px #484444\" src=\"modules/sanseer/media/journals/characters/close-ups/brakefield-cassandra.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></div>\n<hr />\n<p>Daughter to Godfrey Brakefield. She is a chip off his block. She is very astute and also very distrusting of new things and new people until they have proven themselves.</p>\n<p>She has a cruel streak.</p>\n</div>","img":"modules/sanseer/media/journals/characters/portraits/brakefield-cassandra.jpg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"y4pRACjo50IZ62pc":3},"flags":{}}
