{"_id":"MnC1rJalOzO63KeJ","name":"Holly Brakefield","content":"<div style=\"font-family:Signika;text-align:justify;font-size:14px;margin-left:2rem;margin-top:2rem\">\n<div><img style=\"border-radius:50%;border:2px solid black;box-shadow:0 0 25px #484444\" src=\"modules/sanseer/media/journals/characters/close-ups/brakefield-holly.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></div>\n<hr />\n<p>Holly is, essentially, an innocent. Her last birthday saw her turn sixteen. She is doted on by her Grandfather, Godfrey Brakefield, and he has kept her away from the darker side of the family. Perhaps he is attempting some form of redemption for past sins. That does not, however appear to be preventing him from committing new ones it seems.</p>\n<p>Holly was kidnapped a number of days ago, that event being followed by a number of ransom notes.</p>\n</div>","img":"modules/sanseer/media/journals/characters/portraits/brakefield-holly.jpg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"y4pRACjo50IZ62pc":3},"flags":{}}
