{"_id":"QxYKWSrKhuJ4EypK","name":"The Coins Of Ash Keron","content":"<table style=\"font-family:Signika;border-spacing:5px;background-color:transparent;width:630px;max-width:100%;margin-bottom:20px;text-align:justify\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"padding:8px;vertical-align:top;border:1px solid #808080;border-radius:5px;width:50%\">\n<p><img style=\"border:0;margin-left:-5px\" src=\"modules/sanseer/media/journals/coins/nib.png\" width=\"125\" height=\"65\" /></p>\n<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:9px;line-height:18px\">Made from copper. The least of the coins. Very common. The coin of the masses.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"padding:8px;vertical-align:top;border:1px solid #808080;border-radius:5px;width:50%\">\n<p><img style=\"border:0;margin-left:-5px\" src=\"modules/sanseer/media/journals/coins/shard.png\" width=\"125\" height=\"65\" /></p>\n<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:9px;line-height:18px\">Made from a silver coloured alloy. Worth around five copper pieces. Very common. Coin of the masses.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"padding:8px;vertical-align:top;border:1px solid #808080;border-radius:5px;width:50%\">\n<p><img style=\"border:0;margin-left:-5px\" src=\"modules/sanseer/media/journals/coins/sun.png\" width=\"125\" height=\"65\" /></p>\n<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:9px;line-height:18px\">Made from silver. Worth around ten copper pieces. A coin for the relatively affluent.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"padding:8px;vertical-align:top;border:1px solid #808080;border-radius:5px;width:50%\">\n<p><img style=\"border:0;margin-left:-5px\" src=\"modules/sanseer/media/journals/coins/dragon.png\" width=\"125\" height=\"65\" /></p>\n<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:9px;line-height:18px\">Made from gold. Worth ten silver pieces. Uncommon but still plenty to go around. A coin for the afluent.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"padding:8px;vertical-align:top;border:1px solid #808080;border-radius:5px;width:50%\">\n<p><img style=\"border:0;margin-left:-5px\" src=\"modules/sanseer/media/journals/coins/harbour-moon.png\" width=\"125\" height=\"65\" /></p>\n<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:9px;line-height:18px\">Made from a platinum and gold combination. Worth ten gold. Relatively rare coins.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"padding:8px;vertical-align:top;border:1px solid #808080;border-radius:5px;width:50%\">\n<p><img style=\"border:0;margin-left:-5px\" src=\"modules/sanseer/media/journals/coins/taol.png\" width=\"125\" height=\"65\" /></p>\n<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:9px;line-height:18px\">Made from gold and jade. Worth ten Harbour Moon's. Extremely rare coins.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","img":"modules/sanseer/media/journals/coins/all-coins.png","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"y4pRACjo50IZ62pc":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"c7IzEJsoEHJXSe9w","name":"Esmeralda Hayset","content":"<div style=\"font-family:Signika;text-align:justify;font-size:14px;margin-left:2rem;margin-top:2rem\">\n<div><img style=\"border-radius:50%;border:2px solid black;box-shadow:0 0 25px #484444\" src=\"modules/sanseer/media/journals/characters/close-ups/hayset-relda-1.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></div>\n<hr />\n<p>Esmeralda is, of course, a widow now. Having been married to the somewhat abusive, @JournalEntry[DsoostwDcCWbrtFg]{Garan Conway}, a captain of the guards at @JournalEntry[zwoPmdRTNCzjKSgX]{Claybrook Hall}, she became a widow upon Leon's well-placed blow to Conway's jaw during a fight instigated by Conway himself. To a certain degree he had good reason to be that belligerent as Leon had been having an affair with Esmeralda, the two having met during Leon's time a Claybrook Hall. That Esmeralda was physically abused by her husband was one of the main reasons that she fell into a relationship with Leon. Of course, she was as admiring of his charms as he was of hers.</p>\n<p>After her husband's death, she was retained by the Claybrooks. @JournalEntry[97x2utIAqSVb7fEN]{Harland Claybrook} had suspected that his guard captain was hurting Esmeralda but was initially reluctant to step into the relationship between the man and his wife, mainly as a matter of principle. Conway's abuse became too obvious though and Harland eventually had words with Garan Conway about his behaviour. He was most disappointed to find that his words had fallen of deaf ears. Harland perhaps would not have known but his words with Conway most likely resulted in more physical abuse on Esmeralda.</p>\n<p>On the day of his death and prior to trawling round the taverns in the centre of @JournalEntry[wIIvMqJJxCnuPxPB]{Ragarth} and finding Leon, Conway had confronted his wife and left her battered and bleeding at their home. She was found by another lady's maid and the alarm was raised. Esmeralda was only just able to state that her husband had gone to the city looking for Leon. Harland and is brothers and a few men had left Claybrook Hall to find either or both. As it happened all that they did find was a gathering of people around the now deceased Garan Conway.</p>\n<p>They gathered as much information as possible from the witnesses there and organised a man-hunt for Leon. However, the latter had used his skills to avoid being seen leaving Ragarth, ultimately arriving at @JournalEntry[drmEVSH8cvkBtLiH]{Sanseer City}.</p>\n<p>As Esmeralda recovered she was able to relate the whole story to Harland, @JournalEntry[24KQiXOhiDL3CSL2]{Fran Claybrook} and @JournalEntry[w7mrkYSI9N6PknFx]{Evan Claybrook}. The brothers had a great deal of sympathy for Esmeralda and Harland in particular felt some responsibility for her condition, believing that if he had acted more demonstrably and sooner that all of the recent events would have not transpired as they did. Esmeralda believes that the search for Leon was more a matter of being seen to do the right thing, especially as the full story of the fight became known.</p>\n<p>It was suggested to Esmeralda that she remain with the family in their employ should she so wish and that she should, perhaps, revert to her maiden name of Hayset. Evan further suggested that she should use an alternative version of her first name and so she became known as Relda Hayset from that point on.</p>\n<p>She believes that had the Claybrooks caught up with Leon they would have sought some justice or reparation but she suspects that the brothers, on learning the full tale of her life with Conway, felt that her dead husband more or less deserved what had been coming to him.</p>\n<p>Relda will aid Leon and Grim as she still cares for the errant rogue and is grateful that he, despite the extremity of the solution, freed her from \"that bastard of a husband\".</p>\n</div>","img":"modules/sanseer/media/journals/characters/portraits/hayset-relda-1.jpg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"y4pRACjo50IZ62pc":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"drmEVSH8cvkBtLiH","name":"Sanseer","content":"<div style=\"font-family:Signika;text-align:justify;font-size:14px;margin-top:2rem;margin-left:2rem\">\n<h2>What is Sanseer?</h2>\n</div>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"y4pRACjo50IZ62pc":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ezvouBFkGXKJlHCQ","name":"Godfrey Brakefield","content":"<div style=\"font-family:Signika;text-align:justify;font-size:14px;margin-top:2rem;margin-left:2rem\">\n<div><img style=\"border-radius:50%;border:2px solid black;box-shadow:0 0 25px #484444\" src=\"modules/sanseer/media/journals/characters/close-ups/brakefield-godfrey.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></div>\n<hr />\n<p>The head of the Brakefield family, he has held that position since a relatively young age, his parents have died in a fever outbreak that ran amongst some of the higher families. No-one really knew where the disease sprung from.</p>\n<p>He married not much after taking control of the family business and affairs but also, sadly, lost his wife during childbirth. His wife, Alessandra, was indeed much younger than he was at the time they married. He now has a daughter named Cassandra. Rumour is that Godfrey harbours a lingering resentment towards his daughter for the loss of his wife.</p>\n<p>It is thought that the whole experience hardened him. It is a known fact that many, if not all of the 'ruling' families are to some degree corrupt, a result of the power that they wield. The Brakefield's under Godfrey appear to have taken that to deeper levels.</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Godfrey will reward those loyal to him but hammer those who are not. It is generally unwise to get involved in his schemes. However, there are of course those who cannot help themselves and those, like the PCs who have no choice.</p>\n<p>Betraying Godfrey is likely to get you killed.</p>\n</section>\n</div>","img":"modules/sanseer/media/journals/characters/portraits/brakefield-godfrey.jpg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"y4pRACjo50IZ62pc":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"fj21otTBB5oc6Dcs","name":"Meredin","content":"<div style=\"font-family:Signika;text-align:justify;font-size:14px;margin-top:2rem;margin-left:2rem\">\n<h2>What is Meredin?</h2>\n</div>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"y4pRACjo50IZ62pc":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"hwLyX9WDnl7elFvI","name":"Charlon Lugera","content":"<div style=\"font-family:Signika;text-align:justify;font-size:14px;margin-top:2rem;margin-left:2rem\">\n<div><img style=\"border-radius:50%;border:2px solid black;box-shadow:0 0 25px #484444\" src=\"modules/sanseer/media/journals/characters/close-ups/lugera-charlon.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></div>\n<hr />\n<p>A warrior in the ancient legends. Gave her life for her lover @JournalEntry[5MkBZkSfl3WBwwz9]{Variachel Dawnrage}. Variachel dedicated her life to returning Charlon from the afterlife, which she succeeded in doing. The two gracefully left the tribulations of the world behind to live the remainder of their lives together in peace.</p>\n</div>","img":"modules/sanseer/media/journals/characters/portraits/lugera-charlon.jpg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"y4pRACjo50IZ62pc":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"jjZVEFlbu7br7i8N","name":"O'Shan","content":"<div style=\"font-family:Signika;text-align:justify;font-size:14px;margin-top:2rem;margin-left:2rem\">\n<h2>Who is O'Shan?</h2>\n</div>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"y4pRACjo50IZ62pc":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"kGzxoTVtwR3Edq3i","name":"Pir'Lanash","content":"<div style=\"font-family:Signika;text-align:justify;font-size:14px;margin-top:2rem;margin-left:2rem\">\n<h2>Who is Pir'Lanash?</h2>\n</div>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"y4pRACjo50IZ62pc":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"mPTJKSCZFrWRO3F2","name":"Inglis Silver Token","content":"<div style=\"font-family:Signika;text-align:justify;font-size:14px;margin-top:2rem;margin-left:2rem\">\n<p><img style=\"border:0\" src=\"modules/sanseer/media/journals/miscellaneous/inglis-token-a.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Allan Inglis has given you this silver token. He has said his men carry this as an identifying mark (although you could surmise that this is not the only way in which his men or contacts can make themselves known to each other). He has stated that this symbol can be found etched into buildings that are part of his organisation. There a a couple of such buildings in Ragarth and also in Sanseer.</p>\n<p>Presenting this token should grant you either safe passage, safe house, aid or any combination of the three. Given the nature of his business his people have a good knowledge of various cultures and also the people for whom he acquires things. That later knowledge is privileged and confidential. That said, if you make enough impact on Inglis and he \"brings you into the fold\" you may have more access. Who knows how useful that may be in future. He has not yet made you aware of the extent of his organisation structure.</p>\n<p>You get the impression, however, that at least in relation to the abduction of Holly Brakefield that his people will afford you as much aid as possible. They may be constrained by the need to keep themselves on the down low.</p>\n</div>","img":"modules/sanseer/media/journals/miscellaneous/inglis-token-a.png","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"y4pRACjo50IZ62pc":3},"flags":{}}
